description:
Jack Knight visits a sinister circus outside Opal City where he finds a most unsettling freak show--one including a blue-skinned "geek" attraction who may be a former Starman! But Jack's investigation is met with a savage attack from the circus's grotesque performers.

While making his rounds for good deals in Turk County, Jack comes across a circus operated by a Mr. Bliss, and a "Cosmic Geek", Mikaal Tomas.
name: A (K)night at the Circus

description: Superboy faces off against Lady Dragon for the future of mankind. Plus, when a member of Suicide Squad betrays the team, he must answer to one of the deadliest men in the DCU, Deadshot.
name: Watery Grave (Part 3): Honor Among Thieves

description:
Mr Longo has a meeting with a lot of assassins and they are all killed with Joker venom. Artemis fights another superhuman this time trying to save some Rain forest. She gets the Lasso of Truth around him and he suddenly realizes all of the trouble he's caused and the bad person he's been then kills himself.  
 
Diana has been paralyzed by one of Joker's toxins. She spiritually seeks the help of Pan, a God not unlike the Joker. She asks him to teach her his dance so she may understand chaos and that it doesn't control her. He does and she surprises the Joker by ruining the punchline of a joke he's telling. Learning the dance makes her a little loopy and she starts telling her own jokes while she beats him up. The White Magician and Mr. Longo are about to eliminate everyone in the building but Cheetah stops them repaying the debt she feels she owes Diana. Her and the White Magician disappear. Mr. Longo sees Mrs. Sazia trying to escape so he attempts to run her over with her own limo. She says she knows him too well and then blows it up.
name: Boom!

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Story continued from Grifter (1995 1st Series) #1. Deathblow becomes the number one target in the WildStorm Rising crossover! So many Daemonites, so few bullets! Story continues in WetWorks (1994 1st Series Image) #8. Includes a pin-up by David Williams.
name: WildStorm Rising-Chapter 6 of 10

description: Dragon and Takahashi (a.k.a. Okami Red) both train for and then begin their battle, when Freak Force, Vanguard, Liberty, and Justice crash the fight. The assembled heroes battle Okami Red and his forces, then SuperPatriot causes one of Takahashi's weapons to backfire, creating an explosion that lands all of the heroes present in the hospital. The fates of Takahashi and Gaijin are unrevealed.

Spawn had finally made his way back to his home of new york. He is happily welcomed by the homeless that occupy his allies, but the celebration is cut short, when a new Redeemer (Phil Timper) invades spawns alley. Spawn attempts to take down the Redeemer, but is heavily out classed. The Redeemer leaves spawn, broken, beaten, and near death in his alley, while he kidnaps Bobby, and takes him to some unknown angelic place.

However, spawns costume ressurects itself, and evolves to meet this new challenge . . .
name: The Homecoming

description: Flashpoint hunts down Kilgore of the Mercs to learn why Deathtrap held him and his teammates of Stormwatch Prime captive. Kilgore doesn't give him an answer and Flashpoint kills him. When Stormwatch learns of this, they realize they have to take him in. Flashpoint continues to track down the other members of the Mercs, who realize that Kilgore is dead. When he is about to kill Hellslayer, the rest of her teammates arrive. They all battle, with the Mercs nearly killing Flashpoint, when Sunburst and Nautika arrive to apprehend Flashpoint. The three Stormwatch members are able to defeat the Mercs, except for Deathtrap. He tries to flee and Flashpoint blasts away Sunburst so that he can pursue Deathtrap. Nautika arrives to stop Flashpoint, and arrests him, letting Deathtrap go. Meanwhile, Lord Defile makes plans.
Variant, connecting cover by Joe Quesada.
name: Life & Death

description:
Bishop and Magneto have been ambushed by Apocalypse´s forces under his direct command. The leader of the x men has fallen and the mysterious time traveler as well. Now Apocalypse approaches to its final blow. 
 
Pietro and the other x men, has returned from the massive evacuation to find their headquarters empty, now they need to make a decision, save Magneto or Bishop from Apocalypse tyranny!
name: Parents of the Atom

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Wild Child is being chased by a group of Infinites, and is shot in the back. The Infinites are surprised when Holocaust shows up and takes Wild Child prisoner, because he was the one who had dispatched them from Indianapolis. Holocaust tells the Infinites not to question him, and ponders what to do with Wild Child. Finally, he has an idea: they can put on a show! Uncle Joe has some old costumes, and they can use the old barn as a stage!

Before the Infinites can react, Sunfire appears behind them and tells the Infinites to surrender. They refuse. Sunfire thanks, and then vaporizes them. "Holocaust" transforms back into Morph, who chides Sunfire for incinerating his audience. Blink and Rogue teleport in, and ask where Sabretooth is. Wild Child, unable to communicate normally, licks Rogue so she can absorb his memories. Rogue does so, and discovers that Sabretooth and Holocaust are in Indianapolis.

Meanwhile, Sabretooth is having a rough time of it. Holocaust has chained him up and is dragging him through the mud. He regains consciousness and Holocaust shows him the Infinite processing plant. Holocaust and Apocalypse plan on making an army of millions of Infinites to conquer the world. Sabretooth calls Holocaust a loser, because despite all the talk of genetic superiority; he has to stack the deck with artificial soldiers. Holocaust admits to having greater ambitions than just "survival of the fittest", and knocks 'Tooth out again.

On the way to Indianapolis, Blink tells the other X-Men about how Sabretooth rescued her when she was just a child. Morph angers Sunfire due to all of his jokes. Morph tells him that "if he's gonna die, he wants to do it with a smile on his face". Morph then proceeds to start "Singin' in the Rain".

At the X-Men's headquarters in the ruined Xavier Mansion, Magneto is trying to convince Bishop that if it is possible to send him back into the past, he may have to kill Legion(the man who killed Prof. X). Bishop struggles because killing goes against so many of the X-Men's beliefs. Suddenly, Nanny sounds Defcon Armageddon and wraps Magneto's son Charles in a protective shell. Bishop asks Magneto what's going on. Magneto tells him what Defcon Armageddon means: Apocalypse is coming.

Back at the Infinite plant, the soldiers are shocked to find that a giant white whale has swam in through the coolant system. The whale opens his mouth and the X-Men pop out and attack. Morph(having shifted back into his humanoid form) and the rest of the team manage to defeat the Infinites before they can sound the alarm. Blinks screams out "Victor", and 'ports away. Rogue wonders where Blink went, and Morph points over. Blink has found Sabretooth's chained-up body.
name: In Excess

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The Red Skull takes out the Avengers with his “divide and conquer” strategy. Although Black Widow proves to be the most formidable opponent, Red Skull escapes after discovering another EMP abnormality. Could this be the return of the Cosmic Cube?
name: Taking A.I.M. (Prelude): Shadow Hunt

description: Death-Stalker stalks the Sentinel of Liberty as he unravels the mystery of the new Super-Patriot and the diabolical Dead-Ringer!
name: O'er the Ramparts We Watched

description: Cyclops vs. Havok!  Jean Grey captured!  The struggle for control of the breeding pens comes to a shocking climax!  Focusing on Sinister's royal family, this title is fused to the nucleus of the saga! The last ally of Angel has caught so now he must to make a decision! Cyclops is revealed to be the traitor freeing prisoners from the pens, Jean Grey opens the pens.
name: Open Wounds

description:
The X-Ternals finally get a piece of the M'Kraan Crystal. In order to do so, however, Gambit must leave something behind, and it's not just one of his teammates.

Synopsis

The Starjammers take Gambit’s X-Ternals to the heart of the Shi’ar Imporium. The planet is surrounded by a fleet protecting the planet, as well as a newly introduced fusion-energy absorption system (designed to attempt to contain the ever expanding pulses of the M’Kraan Crystal). The Starjammers plan to engage the fleet while Gambit’s team, accompanied by Deathbird, beam to the planet below in order to steal the crystal from Deathbird’s deranged brother, the emperor D’Ken. Once on the planet, the six meet with Imperium troopers. Jubilee, Guido, and Sunspot engage the troops while Gambit, Lila, and Deathbird head off to find and steal the crystal. Jubilee is concerned about her squad’s ability to stay alive; Sunspot confirms that they should be willing to die for this cause.

Gambit’s squad finds that the D’Ken had employed too many troops to the ground fight. There is very little resistance as they make their way to the three-story tall crystal. Wondering how they’ll steal the whole crystal, Deathbird explains that doing so won’t be necessary since a shard of the crystal could hold as much of infinity as the whole crystal. Lila doesn’t get it. Before anything can be explained further, Lila is pulled into the crystal by a blue hand. Gambit argues with Deathbird about following Lila and finally just takes the plunge. Deathbird follows. Inside the crystal, a being named Jahf introduces himself as their host while the universe is destroyed.

Back at the fight, Guido expresses his concern about their chances of success. Sunspot figures it won’t matter either way since the crystal appears to be cracking even more. They experience yet another “blink” in reality and Sunspot notices that his hand turns from its charged state of black to an odd white color. To make matters worse, Gladiator has just joined the fight and he’s brought Rictor with him.

Inside the crystal, Jahf takes Gambit and Deathbird on a stroll through the crystal. The find Lila and D’Ken, oddly transfixed by some red beam of light. When Deathbird tries to kill D’Ken for the wrongs he’s committed, a red beam takes her, as well. Gambit then learns from Jahf the truth of the M’Kraan Crystal. Jahf explains that it is a doorway into all realities; that doorway being the core, the neutron sun. When a door is left open in one reality, other realities cannot help but be affected in one way or another. For example, in what Jahf calls the “actual reality,” Professor Xavier is killed and cannot train Jean in her powers, which means she never became the Phoenix and never fixed the M’Kraan Crystal. Since the crystal was never repaired, all realities are being destroyed by the busted crystal. Gambit is then given the heavy news that his reality was never to have existed in the first place, but he can still save lives by stealing part of the crystal to send Bishop back in time in order to stop the death of Xavier. One catch: Gambit cannot simply take from the crystal – he must leave something behind.

Outside the crystal, Gladiator takes on Sunspot and is surprised when Sunspot turns a fiery white. Another “blink” occurs and Sunspot realizes that he is absorbing power from the M’Kraan Crystal. The troops the squad had been fighting turns to glass and Sunspot orders everyone into the crystal. He even throws Rictor in for a front-row seat. The group sees Gambit and Jahf. Gambit has made his decision about what he’ll leave behind. The only thing anyone hears deals with Rogue. Jahf explains to Gambit that it was because of her that Gambit was sent for the crystal. Gambit strikes out at the crystal and receives a shard. As the group prepares to return to Earth, Sunspot informs them that he’s gathered too much energy. He sacrifices himself by staying behind so as not to jeopardize their plans back on Earth. Realizing that he is right, Lila prepares the X-Ternals for their jump.
name: To The Limits Of Infinity

description:
The Generation Next team have infiltrated Seattle Core on a mission to find and extract the mutant sister of Colossus, Illyana Rasputin. Husk and Vincente are disguised as Quietus, the foreman of Seattle Core, Skin and Chamber are disguised as guards and Mondo is traveling underground to the child labor camp.
 
Skin and Chamber witness a guard indiscriminately kill a child's father for simply offering his daughter some food. Skin has to pull Chamber back or risk them both revealing their identity and blowing cover. Mondo, also a witness, cannot hold back and destroys the balcony the guard was posted at and he falls to his death.
 
Meanwhile, Husk and Vincente have reached Quietus' office and are skillfully keeping up the appearance that they are the administrator of the facility. Sugar Man pays Quietus a visit, and Husk believing their disguise will be seen through cleverly hides in the shower to hide the "stench" that Sugar Man would smell through to reveal their true identities. According to Sugar Man, Apocalypse has gained intel on an X-Men led mission to break into the core and wanted to discuss this with Quietus.
 
Colossus and Shadowcat are poised to phase down into the underground mining facitlity and complete the final phase of the mission. Know-it-all, M counter version, contacts Kitty and Colossus to provide an update on the teams progress and warns them that Skin, Husk, Chamber and Vincente have all been cornered underground. Sugar Man has been told by one of the guards that Chamber and Skin are not security but infiltrators. Sugar Man demands Quietus execute them in front of everyone.
 
Mondo, now 6 miles underground, saves a falling Ace before finding Illyana.
name: It Only Hurts When I Sing

description:
Weapon x embarks on an expedition to Wundagore Mountain, former Magneto´s sanctuary, after several years of no returning. In his path is attacked by two Techno-organic Reavers -Dead-eye and Mangle- but he destroyed them. He arrives to the ruins of Wundagore, home of Gateway, an hermit mutant with teleporting powers, who is secured by Carol Danvers his own bodyguard. 
 
They are ambushed by Reavers -Donald Pierce and Vultura- from the air. Weapon X, Gateway and Danvers teleport to Reaver´s plane, later Danvers jumps with Pierce out of the plane, in mid air she blows up a granade sacrificing her trying to kill Pierce.
name: The common right of toads and men
What if the Kingpin Owned Daredevil

description:
Mother and son has reunited, the Darkholmes are arriving to Avalon, despite a reluctant Mystique. With them has come the assassins, known as pale riders, of Apocalypse and the final battle of Avalon has begun.  
 
Changing sides, death, assembling a team and the destruction of the paradise!
name: Body Heat

description: Domino has reached the Outcasts and claims to see the Telepath, Forge is gaining time to Nate could scape but X-Man has another plan. The assassins do not have regrets and want to do the job for which they were hired by the Dark Lord. Many lives will be lost in this final fight but Nate could find his own path. The final revelation of the true identity of Essex and the last breath of a father!
name: Turning Point

description: The fate of Marvel Universe during the Age of Apocalypse has revealed! What happened with the mightiest heroes on Earth? The rage of Apocalypse has arrived to Euroasia.
name: Last Stand

description: Oakroot, son of Freefot, the seventh of the Wolfrider chieftains foresees a time of declining The High-Ones heritage in his efl-tribe. He remembers Eldolil, the last of the pure blooded elves, seeking him out. Eldolil is by then a shrivelled hermit who lives in the mountains, who is nearly subdued completely by old-age. Eldolil passes on the key for Oakroot's remembrance as Chief, and this is to be more elf than woolf.
name: HOWL FOR ELDOLIL

description:
The wolfriders have finally settled into their new hold, on top of a craggy hill, with a natural rock formation resembling a howling wolf.
The original Wolfriders are each very pleased with Ember for leading the tribe to new prosperity and security. This is her chance to separate herself, and she begins to flirt with Teir, who continues to decline the invitation to become part of her clan.
They are called to speak in council, where Ember declares "Howling Rock" the official new dwelling place.
name: MESSENGER

description:
A copy of this work may be found in the elfQuest archives, at http://www.elfQuest.com

The Title of this issue "TURNABOUT" indicates several elements within the overall theme of elfQuest SHARDs:

  1. the Human VenoVel is becoming more elflike
  2. The townsfolk no longer believe in Grohmul Djun's sovereignty, impeccability, or divinity
  3. Shuna is now looked upon as stronger than her Father, a Centennial for the Djun

Costume: Green Shawl

The transition also occurs rather brilliantly through the stage costume of the Human patriots. Shuna has an ally in an unnamed male with long brown hair, who wears the same style of green shaul-sweater. Although Shuna is not featured in this issue at all, Aroree, being as tall as a human wears a green cloack in order to walk amongst the humans.

This is the beginning of Rayek's long sleep inside the SHARDroom, he became subdued and eventuall inherited the soul/spirit of Winnowill.

Mender and Flam start a fight, and this alerts the Djun's men against them. Inside the soldiers kill a man and almost kill two human children, but instead, Flam kills the soldiers.
name: TURNABOUT

description:
Alt title Hide & Seek.

This is probably the best example of the wonderful display of all sorts of futuristic designs that the people projected during the decade of the 90's. Featured on a spacestation orbitting planet Abode, In this issue, Jink shapechanges into human and sneaks onto the ship to declare her love for Kullyn Kenn. Then Jink the heroic space-traveller must face the Neverending.
name: CONVERGENCE

description:
Guest-starring the 30th Century Silver Surfer! Starhawk steals the Surfer's Quantum Bands! Can his vast powers survive the combined assult of Eon, the Surfer, and the Hawkgod?! Plus: Starhawk discovers who his real father is!

Second Story: 'Homeward Bound' Yellowjacket Rita DeMara, reaches a planet where time travel is a specialty and a service sold the same way as travel agencies.
name: What Child Is This
Things Fall Apart

description: The battle between the Armorines and the guerrilla fighters heats up. And matters get worse when the Armorines realize that weapons dealer Arturo Vasquez sold his advanced weaponry to both Castro and the guerrilla fighters!
name: The Cuban Connection, Part 2 - Crossfire

description: Werewolf, Part 1 of 3. The murder of two Wayne Tech employees leads the Dark Knight to London and into the British underworld, bringing Batman face to face with a different kind of killer...a werewolf.
name: Werewolf Part 1 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: The Fantastic Force journey into The Negative Zone in order to save The Invisible Woman from certain death. When they exit the Negative Zone however they find themselves at the heart of an epic conflict between The Watchers and their greatest enemies...The Celestials.
name: The Masque of Doom!
Lessons

description: "The War for Arcadia" reaches its penultimate chapter, and the victor is... Lord Alamout? Gamble? Coffin? X... or is it X? Confused? You won't be after reading this issue. The war is about to end, and the body count is rising. Will X survive? Who will win control of the most corrupt city in America? Or will the city itself become a casualty of war?
name: Penultimatum

description: An injured Dark Knight must rip apart Blue Byrd's turbulent past to learn who is trying to silence the reborn musician forever.
name: Playing Changes

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight: Jazz

description: Black Panther assists with a retilian problem near the Savage Land.
name: Spawn

description: The Joker's stand-up comedy has a literal captive audience.
name: Falls Upon The Joker: Part Two: Tears of a Clown

description:
Overview

It's the shortest day of the year in the heart of the Big Apple and, for some, the last day. Maximillian "Quasimodo" Steel has found The Truth and all who stand in his way are targets. Her Majesty's finest, James Bond, is ready to stop him any way possible, but there's a final wild card in this deck and no one may live to see the light of tomorrow!

Prologue to 'The Death of Clark Kent,' a 7-part storyline beginning in Superman #100. Attempts are made upon Clark Kent's life, leaving no doubt that one of Superman's deadliest foes has learned the truth of his dual identity.

Notes:

  • Superman is making a peanut butter sandwich with Super-Chunk Peanut Butter. A homage to the Superman Peanut Butter food product of the 1980s.
  • Perry White's license plate number is CZRS-GST for Caesar's Ghost.
  • Last $1.50 issue.
  • Last paper and color format used. The next issue uses heavier stock paper and glossy pages.
  • Triangle 1995 #17.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #709.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #100.
name: To Know... Know... Know Him!

description: Rosie Nolan was an ordinary girl until the day her violent paranormal powers first erupted. Seeking to gain control of her abilities, Rosie embarks on a desperate quest across the globe, aided by a radical animal rights activist, hounded by an obsessed C.I.A agent, and hunted by a corrupt British cop.
name: Dangerous to Man

description: grell
name: Bar Sinister

description:
Gilad sets out to stop his son. Using his girlfriend as bait Gilad lures his son out so that he can end his madness once and for all. But should he be careful what he wishes for? He'll soon find himself in the fight of his life!

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Mortal Kin - Part 2: Faint And Parry

description: With his wife still held hostage by the robotic right to life alliance, Magnus tries to rescue her and then finds that they have fled and he’ll have to hunt them down in “Hardened Heart.”
name: Hardened Heart
Steel, Meat, & Potatoes - Part Two: All Along The Watchtower

Turok and company have entered the timestream and where will it take them? To a tribe in the far past that was once enslaved by the Mothergod and now needs help.

Original cover color-art by Bill Dunn - see pic below.

- Campaigner

- Seer (Merlin)
name: The Prodigal - Part 1:Intermission

description:
Flip book w/ "Apu Nahasapeemapetilon's Kwik-E-Comics #1." Cover pencils by Bill Morrison, inks by Alexander. Fan-Tasty Island, script by Jeff Rosenthal, pencils by Luis Escobar (Layouts) and Tim Bavington (Pencils), inks by Tim Bavington, Bill Morrison, Robert Kramer, and David Mowry; Mr. Burns uses the Simpsons to smuggle a secret energy source into the country. Matt Groening talks about the bad haircuts he used to get as a child. Apu's Incredible 96 Hour Shift (Without Having a Break!), script by Bill Morrison, art by Shawn Cashman; Apu is trapped inside the Kwik-E-Mart for 96 hours, with a wanted man.

  1. Fan-Tasty Island
  2. Why Bart's Hair is so Spiky, Part One (full text article by Matt Groening)
  3. Junk Mail (letters column)
  4. Apu Nahasapeemapetilon's Kwik-E-Comics #1
  5. Apu's Incredible 96 Hour Shift (Without Having a Break!)
name: Bummer Vacation!
Things that go Bump in the Night

description:
Overview

Some people will tell you every ending is a new beginning. Others think of endings in less gentle terms, like driving your car screaming into the back wall of a dark alley. Scott Tolson and the Colors in Black crew have gassed up for the final issue of this critically acclaimed miniseries. In "Blue," a black boxer pounds a lesson into his opponents about the hard knocks of being a shade darker. "Jap You're Next" dwells in the nightmare world of a mistrust that has lasted for generations. An American-born Chinese takes out his jealous anger on a well-to-do Taiwanese immigrant, but the two find that they share mutual enemies in "American Born." And finally, in "Hand of God," a young black man finds powerful logic in the "eye-for-an-eye" philosophy.

You know when you fill up your tank, and the little arrow in your fuel gauge goes beyond the full mark? That feeling like you've got enough gas to go around the globe twice, only stopping for things like Jolt cola and pecan logs? That's how Schreck feels editing DHP, 'cause this issue is more than full. First up, he's got the penultimate chapter of the spaghetti-western/samurai spoof, "A Pot Full of Noodles," by Rennie and Langridge, in which The Kabuki Kid and his faithful sidekick Lu-Win encounter the Evil Factory Man and his Droidzilloid -- fast, furious, and fun! Then the plot thickens for private eye Hal, as Ed "Lowlife" Brubaker and Stefano Gaudiano conclude "Here and Now." And finally, in "The Picture of Doreen Grey" the Kid goes Eyeballs-to-the-wall in an all-out assault against the Body Corporation, while Joe's lost in his own nirvana. So Schreck tears outta this issue with his gauge still past full, and he's burning rubber heading toward the big five-part DHP 100 blowout! If you're real nice, he'll let you ride shotgun!

Trapped on a drone barge headed for a recycling center, See-Threepio is about to have his memory wiped clean! Artoo races to rescue his old pal, but will Threepio even recognize the the plucky little droid by the time he arrives?
name: Rebellion, Part 3 of 4

description:
Red Hot Riding Hood is goin' to Granny's for a friendly visit and a little snack. But Wolfy wants to do a little visiting of his own, and he'll stop at nothing to corral that tomato Red! Oh, Gramma, what big fun you'll have in "Li'l Ridin' Red"!

Meanwhile, in the back of the comic, Wolfy the Pirate spies booty aplenty on a distant sailing ship: a treasure chest overflowing with gold and a chesty treasure in a hot Red dress! First he'll steal the loot, he reasons, then he'll steal a kiss! But he's gonna have to get through the virile Captain Droopy to do it, in a little number we call "Pirates Ho"!
name: Li'l Ridin' Red; Pirates Ho!

description:
Part 6 of the 7-part 'The Death of Clark Kent.' Superman may not be able to control himself when he faces the man who has destroyed both of his lives.

Notes:

  • Superman doesn't appear in this issue. He appears as his temporary alias of Wayne Jordan.
  • Jonathan Kent takes the temporary alias of Gilbert Jordan.
  • First $1.95 issue.
  • New paper and color format introduced. The issue is heavier and the pages glossier.
  • Triangle 1995 #23.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #101.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #711.
name: Where is Superman?

description: "A Bedtime Story" Trapped aboard an alien craft, Maxine enters a disturbing alternative reality of storybook nightmares.
name: A Bedtime Story

description:
Azrael, Brian and two new allies journey to northern Africa in search of the secret of the System. Their perilous quest grows even more deadly when the trail leads to the infamous immortal, Ra's al Ghul, and his mysterious daughter, Talia!

Jean Paul, Lilhy, and Brian escaped and contacted Oracle. They made way for Mobari to seek the teachers of the system. Ra's al Ghul learned they'd arrived near his territory. His people captured them.
name: Fallen Angel 5: The Abduction

description:
The Dark Knight must find out whom the Black Spider is planning to assassinate before gang warfare erupts across Gotham City.

James Gordon quits the Gotham police force. His wife Sarah Essen succeeds him as Commissioner.

Black Spider reported to his real boss, "Ottoman Turk." Mayor Krol, hoping to help his reelection bid, demoted James Gordon and replaced him with his wife, Sarah Essen-Gordon. The former Commissioner single-handedly took down Gotham's most wanted - Tommy "Mangles." After the collar, he turned in his badge. Batman got on the trail of Black Spider and his two bosses. He easily took him down, but Black Mask escaped.
name: Black Spider: Web of Scars

description:
Part 2 of the 2-part 'Small Glass Worlds.' Tim and Titania have an unlikely reunion as the question of Tim Hunter's true parentage is settled once and for all.

Salamander is reduced to trying to sell magic items on the street after the destruction of Slaggingham's sewer base. Titania and the Amadan, in London, pass by him with condescension.

Tim and Molly finally get to have some ice cream, and are observed by Circe, a tattoo artist.

Staylace--now going by her first name, Gwendolyn--runs into Tim and Molly, and introduces them to Auberon, who still hasn't put his soul back in his body. A mental construct of Gwendolyn teaches Auberon's soul about being responsible within the globe.

Marya (protected by the unicorn) and Daniel argue; he feels she ran out on him, but she just wanted to grow up in the real world. The unicorn stabs Daniel after he slaps Marya. Daniels leaves.

Gwen wants Tim to help Auberon, but Tim gets worried once he realizes that he's Titania's husband. He tries, but can't figure out how to do it. Then Titania shows up. She is angry at having to deal with the humans, and at the mess Auberon has gotten himself into. She tries to get the globe from Tim, but it falls and breaks. Titania is about to wreak terror on them all in revenge for his presumably-lost soul, but it turns out that it went back into his body after all.

Auberon feels that he has learned something from being among the mortals, and stops Titania. He wants to start a new relationship with her, after only playing at love for centuries. He also asks Tim and Titania if Tim is her son, and she admits that it is true, and that Tamlin is the father.

However, Auberon says that Tim has no fairy blood, and so cannot be Titania's son, although he does look like Tamlin. Auberon and Titania leave, with Tim once more unsure of his parentage. (This is wrapped up much later in the Books of Faerie, where it turns out that Titania was actually originally human as well, and so it is true that she is his mother, and that Tim's parents are both human.)
name: Small Glass Worlds, Part II: Transparent Lies

description: Part 1 of the 3-part 'Picking Up the Pieces.' Green Lantern guest-stars as Damage must deal with the consequences of his recent search for his true origin, including the funeral of someone close and a tense reunion with the New Titans.
name: Picking Up the Pieces, Chapter One

description:
As the terminally ill Firestorm's powers reassert themselves full blast, his elemental aspect returns to Earth to reclaim his human half. But when Raymond resists, Captain Atom and the Justice League must prevent the Nuclear Man and the Fire Elemental from destroying each other.

The Extreme Justice team witness the return of the elemental Firestorm, Martin Stein, back to Earth to be reunited with Ronnie Raymond. He wants Ronnie to merge consciousnesses with him, to allow Ronnie to witness everything he has seen in the universe. However, the elemental Firestorm is unaware of the property damage he is creating by just his presence. The Extreme Justice team rush to control the damage, while Captain Atom tries to get the elemental Firestorm to stop. Elemental Firestorm bats Captain Atom away, all the while elatedly telling Ronnie the stories of what he has seen. Finally, Ronnie gets Stein to calm down, and assume a less damaging form. Ronnie declines Stein’s offer to travel the cosmos. Stein is saddened, but honors Ronnie’s request. Stein returns to space, but as a parting gift, cures Ronnie of his cancer and restores his transmutative powers. With nowhere else to go, Ronnie accepts Captain Atom’s offer to join Extreme Justice as Firestorm.
name: Atomic Nights

description: Jared battles L'Intern, rescued by the guardian angel who gets his arm cut off by the knife. Later, Qabala rescues them from a crowd and Jared returns to L'Intern's to retrieve his knife.
name: Will to Darkness!

description: Flash battles Mongul. Wally's relationship with Linda has also been strained since his return from the Speed Force.
name: Running Away

description:
It's the rematch of the century as Hal Jordan, the uber-powerful Parallax, battles Kyle Rayner for the right to bear the Green Lantern power ring.

Ganthet and Hal argue about which of them should get the ring but Kyle refuses to hand it over to anyone. Hal grabs him and Kyle lashes out. Fighting ensues, Kyle is no match for Hal or that’s what Ganthet thinks so he teleports away for people who stand a chance.

Martian Manhunter, Aquaman, Flash, Hawkman, Superman and Green Arrow are called. Kyle hold his own valiantly despite Hal’s superior power, skill and experience. In the end Kyle falls and Hal prepares to take the ring. Ganthet arrives with his team.
name: Parallax View: The Resurrection of Hal Jordan, Part 1

description: ""Dreamtime"" part 2! Constantine devises an ingenious double-reverse in his struggle to stop the Rainbow Serpent, a brutal aboriginal deity that intends to purge Earth of all animal life.
name: Dangerous Ground

description: Impulse's first day at school gains him the ire of several violent cliques of students. Impulse somewhat innocently manipulates the groups into confronting each other, causing everyone but him to get into a great deal of trouble.
name: How to Win Friends and Influence People

description:
Shell-shocked from recent events, Dane quits the Invisibles, causing turbulence within the team. And as the Invisibles' enemies continue plotting their destruction, the story of John-A-Dreams, Dane's predecessor, is revealed.

The issue begins with a flashback to three years ago, in the Philadelphia of 1992. King Mob (with hair!) and Jonn-a-Dreams are investigating a church, searching for the Hand of Glory. King Mob tells John that they should have called in reinforcements, but John feels that there wasn't enough time. The two invisibles walk past a crucified toad, and into a darkened room with a horrible smell. The enter; and KM shines his flashlight on what seems to be a bizarre conglomeration of organic matter. John remarks that it's marvelous; while KM disagrees. He asks his partner if whatever it is, is dead. John tells him that THAT one is. John explains that he thinks that they're just vehicles made from organic stuff to give the user some sort of physical presence. John notices another door behind some blue mushrooms. Despite King Mob's protestations, he opens it. The Invisible's jaws drop when they see...

In the present of 1995, Boy and Lord Fanny are trying to antisept Jack's mutilated finger. Meanwhile, Jack is furious and has had enough of the Invisibles and their shenanigans. King Mob turns from his reminiscing and tells the group that he has a feeling that things may be worse than they thought. Outside, a group of myrmidons approach the windmill. The myrmidon leader tells his men that this is payback for what the Invisibles did to them Soho.

Back inside, King Mob has told the group who he thinks could be responsible for giving the enemy their time travel codes. Jack, however, couldn't care less. KM suspects that their traitor could be John-a-Dreams, who had been taken through a fracture and considered to be dead. Fanny comes to John's defense, but as KM points out; who else could it be? Nobody has paid much attention to Jack's complaining, and he prepares to leave. Ragged Robin tells them that trouble in the form of myrmidons is coming. King Mob decries their strategic position, and decides that their best bet is to try to get to their cars parked outside. Jack smiles...

King Mob reaches for his gun, only to realize that it's missing. Fanny tells him that Jack had it when he tried to shoot Orlando. She asks Jack what he did with it; only to realize that Jack is gone. Boy goes rushing after him, but is too late and can only watch as he goes driving away in King Mob's sportscar. She goes back inside to tell the others. KM slaps his head in frustration and reveals that his car has "explosive" security features. If Jack doesn't enter the passcode, he has about four minutes to live. Ragged Robin senses the myrmidons coming out of the trees. KM forces himself to stop worrying about Jack, and asks anybody if they have any weapons. Unfortunately, all they have is Fanny's lighter. Boy suggests Orlando's pruning shears, laying next to his white coat. This gives King Mob an idea.

Elsewhere, Jack drives King Mob's car at 80 MPH through a myrmidon barricade; causing him to lose control and wreck into a tree.

The myrmidons enter the windmill and call out Orlando's name. One of soldiers admits that he finds Orlando kind of creepy. The myrmidons climb to the top of the windmill, where the Invisibles are collapsed on the floor. Orlando tells the drones that the boy escaped, but none of the others are dead. Suddenly, "Orlando" pulls out a knife and stabs the myrmidon in the stomach. Boy jumps up and disarms a myrmidon, while King Mob(the fake Orlando) takes the fallen myrmidon's firearm and blasts the remaining soldiers. KM tells the Invisibles that's four of the myrmidons down, and he informs the group that now they need smoke. "Lots of it".

Jack crawls out of the wrecked vehicle, and is stopped by a myrmidon holding a gun. Jack raises his arms in surrender, but is saved by the exploding car. The blast kills the soldiers, and knocks Jack into the nearby stream.

A myrmidon comes staggering out of the smoking windmill; telling the others that the Invisibles have used gas. He collapses, and one soldier runs over to help him up. The fallen "myrmidon" pulls out a gun and starts blasting away at his fellow soldiers. The myrmidons are in a state of total confusion as the Invisible's other car drives forward and runs them over.

Meanwhile, Jack is crawling out of the stream, gasping for air. A myrmidon soldier steps in front of him and tells the youth that it's over. Jack pulls out a gun and fires...

King Mob pulls of the myrmidon mask as he joins his teammates in the car. He opens the window and begins shooting while Robin drives. They work their way forward for a bit, until KM spies the burning remains of his sportscar. They get out and search for any signs of Jack, but all they can find are dead soldiers. King Mob makes some morbid jokes, causing Boy to chastise him. After searching for a few minutes they discover Jack's tracks, which seemingly vanish(when he was knocked into the river). King Mob decides they need to call in Mister Six.

As the sun rises, Jack stands over the fallen myrmidon and realizes that he just killed a man. He drops the gun and cries out in anguish.
name: 23: Things Fall Apart

description: Johnny and Edgar are the Autumn brothers: half man, half worm, and all mean. They're out to kill Hex, but Jonah and the singing cowboys aim to bring the battle straight to the mother worm herself.

volume.name: Jonah Hex: Riders of the Worm and Such

description:
The Justice League has long been the nexus of super-hero activity in the DC Universe. Its new airborne base of operations has yielded secrets and resources to stagger the imagination. Now the League takes its status a step further by opening its headquarters to heroes throughout the world. But the revitalized Lord Havok seizes this opportunity to strike at the League, and not even Warrior's return can tip the scales in the League's favor, especially when the team learns the senses-shattering secret behind Havok's return.

Notes:

  • Both newstand and deluxe foil covers penciled by Chuck Wojtkiewicz and inked by Bob Dvorak.
  • 48 page issue.
  • "Keith, Marc and Andy" credited as Ghostly Trio.
name: Opening Up the Game

description: Von Mauler is obsessed with Gypsy, and nothing, not even a maximum security prison, will keep him from having her.

As Sheriff Root and his hideously deformed son set out in pursuit of Jesse and Tulip, the vampire Cassidy faces the Saint of Killers. Meanwhile, angels have begun their own pursuit of the being that has merged with Jesse.

Cassidy leaves the group after revealing he's a vampire; Jesse and Tulip talk about their past and Genesis; Sheriff Root tries to recover his honor.
name: And The Horse You Rode In On

description:
(continued from Detective 685)

Robin witnessed the first stages of the brewing mob war and contacted Bruce. He saw Huntress swoop down on the fight between Lynx and King Snake and went to her aid. Dorrance fled; Batman gave chase. Silver Monkey attacked Batman and threatened him over the King Snake Bounty.

(continued in Detective 686)
name: War of the Dragons, Part 2: The Silk Dragons

description: Without the help of his precognitive dreams or the sustaining love of Dian, Wesley Dodds may well become the Butcher's next meal.
name: Night of the Butcher: Act 3 of 4

description: Part 2 of the 5-part 'Nasty Infections.' Shade's friends descend into pandemonium as the strange events befalling them become increasingly bizarre.
name: Nasty Infections, Part Two: Rotten Pot

description: A Wolf in Cheap Clothing, Part 4 of 4. Kirk learns that a sacred relic of the Klingon people has been stolen - one that could cause the downfall of the Klingon High Council and plunge the Empire into anarchy.
name: A Wolf...In Cheap Clothing The Conclusion!

description: Part 2 of 5. A Tholian commander bent on vengeance lures the Starship Enterprise into the Tholians' infamous web.
name: War and Madness Part II: A Handful of Dust

description:
Jack Knight returns to the freak show to free the alien Starman one way or another. But will both Starmen be able to cope with the price of freedom? Plus, a figure from Opal City's past begins to awaken, and a mysterious demon poster returns with its equally mysterious owner.

While bargain-hunting with farmers in Turk County, Jack Knight comes upon a circus, operated by a man named Bliss, and home for a number of freaks including a Cosmic Geek. The other freaks enlist him to champion their escape from Bliss and his assistant Crusher.
name: A (K)night at the Circus II

description: Superboy attends his first day at Ilupani High School, and he soon finds himself in one-on-one combat with the hulking bruiser known as Loose Cannon.
name: School and Hard Knocks

description:
“River Run” continues: Swamp Thing's odyssey through parallel worlds leads him to a dark bayou where an aged, semiretired superhero must defeat Solomon Grundy and uncover a terrible secret.

In the fourth story of River Run, The Secret of Slaughter Swamp, Swamp Thing must take on the form of Solomon Grundy, and reveal to a semi-retired superhero named the Black Box the secrets of Slaughter Swamp, including one very dark secret belonging to his wife.

Note: This chapter is inspired in the earth-2 concept from the pre-crisis multiverse.
name: The Secret of Slaughter Swamp: Chapter Four of River Run

description:
Artemis confronts Diana furious that she let the Joker get away and that violence and crime are in her home city. She says she's accomplished more in 4 months than Diana did in 4 years, and really talks down to her then storms off. Artemis goes to Mrs. Sazia's house to take her down next and fights her way through hordes of robotic guards. Inside she meets a hologram of Mrs. Sazia and the hologram explains the house has defenses and Artemis is ensnared by lots of extremely durable tentacles. The house explodes just as Artemis escapes.  
 
Diana visits one of the super humans Artemis fought and learns that he's an actor. On her back she flies past the people working with Artemis and Artemis cheap shots her in the sky claiming Boston is HER city. They start to fight and Diana throws her through a building after Artemis lands a good kick. Diana rips out a filing cabinet and tells Artemis that the men were using her as entertainment. The issue ends with Diana stating she is going back to Themyscira for some real answers and that she's been fighting the wrong person.
name: Sisters!

description: Sarah, framed for vandalism, finds herself in the jail cell with the Is. And Sarah has finaly finished listening to all of her dad’s tapes and knows everything. She manages to kill the Is but not before it kills the thug in the next cell.

The Fiend confronts and possesses Debbie Harris' mother. Meanwhile, Dragon searches for the Octopus creature, and is joined by Star.

There are two issue 13's. The previous issue was 13 created by fellow Image creator Jim Lee. Erik Larsen went on to create this different issue 13 later on. This issue is sometimes notated as #13b
